# YT Multistream Workflow Rule

- Preserve operation-console UX: queue, config panel, runtime console, and clear stream states.
- Keep feature work aligned to multistream lifecycle: setup -> run -> monitor -> recover.
- Validate stream config before start: source + RTMP base + stream key.
- Keep ffmpeg process management robust and avoid orphan workers.
- Never expose full stream keys in logs or UI summaries.
- Prefer modular architecture as code grows: UI, queue logic, IPC contracts, and process control.
- For source parsing, keep Google Drive URL handling in a dedicated helper.
- Run `corepack pnpm build` after substantive changes and report what was verified.
